choices.text:
football. For real, it’s a healthy obsession. Every house in all cities and villages own one TV or more. So “football” is just part in the evening meal. Some homes actually even name themselves after football squads: St Eusebe FC, BanquePrivee Zun La Police, Atletico Barikad CFP, Reconciliation Club Skie and Coton Sport.

Exams? Not me, I’ll just lie

A Togolese student scoring one point in O- Level is the same as me scoring thirty; because he just has to forego his diploma and pass it the next time. But I prefer sticking to my own system- I prefer applying for make up exams.

Never easing off the public transportation

The president opens (well, funds) a class car that he can offer to some thirty kids. In a country of seven million people, only two million have cars. There’s always over-crowding hence the favourite is the bicycle. No need of draft releases, just lie still and keep steady. Unless you want to be thrown back.

Scrapping for the bus’ tiny space

A Togolese public bus’s space is too small for three adults. Well, unless you are a man. Therefore, some have put up a ladder. True story.

Healthcare sucks

Are you a single gal and living in Togo or you live with your newly wedded husband? Sorry no maternity wards. Child birth is free
